This paper discusses the maximal degree of Gabriel and Yao graphs, which are commonly used in wireless ad-hoc networks. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the growth of the maximal degree, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper may involve some information theory, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory).
